      "side": 1,
      "message": "The last check `return ticks ? ticks : 1;` seems redundant, as we\u0027ve already checked that the number of seconds is non-zero.\n\nCould we simplify the logic ? i.e.\n\n```\n  sfdp_seconds_to_ticks (f64 seconds)\n  {\n    if (seconds \u003c\u003d 0)\n      return 0;\n\n    f64 interval \u003d sfdp_timer_interval_sec ();\n    u32 ticks \u003d (u32) (seconds / interval);\n    if (ticks * interval \u003c seconds)\n      ticks++;\n\n    return ticks;\n  }\n```",
      "revId": "79f04ccf42ba6014a0371499d915943b3b78790d",
